snippet: House Republicans’ victory in federal court last week, if upheld on appeal, would block the administration from reimbursing insurers for discounts to low-income people.
abstract: Millions of Obamacare customers could face higher premiums, pending administration's appeal of federal court ruling prohibiting government subsidies for low-income people; suit brought by House Republicans asserted bypassing congressional authorization to compensate insurers for discounts provided to poor people is unconstitutional.
lead_paragraph: House Republicans’ victory in federal court last week, if upheld on appeal, would block the administration from reimbursing insurers for discounts to low-income people.

headline.main: House Challenge to Health Law Could Raise Premiums, Administration Says
headline.print_headline: Health Law Challenge May Raise Rates
